# OPS/_llm/200 — react to a finished exchange.
#
# After the upstream stream ends, the gateway fires a second envelope
# into this same stack with @llm.phase == "completed" — the client
# never waits on it. @llm.completion carries the transfer facts
# (status, duration_ms, bytes_in, bytes_out, model, stream,
# client_disconnected), ready for billing counters, audit trails, or a
# kv/incr. This demo just stamps a marker so the completion run is
# visible in the trace.
WHEN @src == "llm" && @llm.phase == "completed"
  EMIT .audit = "llm request completed"
